  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Top, tail, peel and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop your <strong>parsnip[s]</strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Dice your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on), then crush 3 <span class=\"text-purple\">[4]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[6]</span> of the <strong>garlic cloves</strong> with the side of your knife (keeping the skins on)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1014.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1014.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1014.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1014.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1014.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped carrot</strong>,<strong> parsnip</strong>, <strong>potato</strong> and <strong>crushed garlic </strong>to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the baking tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until the <strong>vegetables</strong> are tender and browned</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
