    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve <strong>half </strong>your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> (save the rest for later!) in 150ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [220ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>chicken stock, panko breadcrumbs</strong> and the <strong>sage & onion butter</strong> in a bowl and set aside to cool and absorb the liquid</p><p>Meanwhile, place your hand flat onto your <strong>chicken breast fillet[s]</strong></p><p>Slice in half as if you were cutting a burger bun, so you are left with two thinner pieces</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
