    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[320ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span>[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to the pan and stir for 30 secs</p><p>Stir in the <strong>chicken stock</strong> and<strong> Henderson's Relish</strong> and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the gravy has thickened</p><p>Once cooked, remove the <strong>chicken</strong> and slice finely</p>",
